7. Performance

Q1. Will this be slower than a human?

This will definitely come.

Answer

Performance is one of our primary NFRs.

We target execution that is comparable to or faster than manual execution by:

* Choosing MCP over browser interaction whenever possible
* Minimizing LLM reasoning
* Runtime validation instead of repeated planning
* Cached workflow execution

⸻

Q2. Why Planner after every step?

Answer

We don’t necessarily replan after every action.

The planner generates a short execution horizon.

Replanning occurs only when runtime validation detects deviation.

⸻

