11. Architecture

This is where I expect Kranthi to spend most of his time.

Q1. Why MCP?

Answer exactly as we discussed.

MCP provides a more stable and maintainable integration path. Where available, it is preferred over browser automation because UI interactions are inherently more susceptible to change.

⸻

Q2. Why Browser?

Not every enterprise system exposes MCP capabilities. Browser interaction enables WebGenie to orchestrate complete business workflows across heterogeneous enterprise systems.

⸻

Q3. Why both?

Enterprise business workflows span multiple systems. Using only one integration mechanism would limit the platform. WebGenie selects the most appropriate execution mechanism for each system within the workflow.

⸻

12. AI Questions

These will definitely come.

Why Agentic AI?

Because business workflows require:

* reasoning
* planning
* adapting to runtime changes
* coordinating multiple systems

Traditional automation cannot dynamically make these decisions.

⸻

Why not deterministic workflows?

Deterministic workflows work well for predefined processes.

Agentic AI enables users to describe goals in natural language and dynamically generate or adapt workflows when appropriate, while still allowing successful executions to be refined into stable, reusable workflows.

⸻

13. One Question I Personally Expect

After talking with you for weeks, I think Kranthi will ask this.

How do you ensure the planner doesn’t hallucinate?

I’d answer:

The planner never directly manipulates the browser. It proposes the next action, which is validated against the live browser state before execution. Runtime validation acts as a safety layer, ensuring only valid actions are performed. Additionally, sensitive operations require human approval based on enterprise policies.
